# Recurring Tasks Implementation

**Date:** 2025-11-26
**Status:** Planning
**Priority:** P1 - HIGH (Competitive Parity)
**Estimated Time:** 12-16 hours

---

## Overview

Implement recurring tasks for Kanban board to match competitive feature parity. All major competitors (Asana, ClickUp, Todoist, Monday.com) have recurring tasks as a fundamental feature.

**User Need:**
Users need tasks that repeat on a schedule (daily standup, weekly review, monthly reports) without manual duplication.

**Technical Challenge:**
Need to add recurrence to Task type, generate instances on demand, handle completion vs instance completion, and provide intuitive UI.

---

## Problem Statement

**Current Behavior:**
- Tasks are one-time only
- Users must manually duplicate tasks for recurring workflows
- No automation for repeating tasks
- Calendar Events have recurrence but Tasks do not

**Desired Behavior:**
- Tasks can be set to recur (daily, weekly, monthly, yearly)
- New instances generated automatically based on schedule
- Completing an instance doesn't delete the parent task
- Edit options: "This instance" vs "All future instances"
- Clean UI for setting recurrence patterns

**User Impact:**
- HIGH - This is table stakes feature for task management
- All competitors have this
- Critical for workflows like:
  - Daily standups
  - Weekly reviews
  - Monthly reports
  - Quarterly planning
  - Annual reviews

